278 /*!******************************************************************************
279  * \brief Send a video p_packet to decoder
280  *
281  * \param
282  *
283  * \return
284  *******************************************************************************/
285 int ni_decoder_session_write(ni_session_context_t* p_ctx, ni_packet_t* p_packet)
286 {
287  ni_nvme_result_t nvme_result = 0;
288  ni_nvme_command_t cmd = { 0 };
289  uint32_t sent_size = 0;
290  uint32_t packet_size = 0;
291  uint32_t read_size_bytes = 0;
292  uint32_t metadata_size = 0;
293  int retval = NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS;
294  static int count = 1;
295  static uint32_t packets_sent = 0;
296 
297  ni_debug_print("ni_decoder_session_write(): enter\n");
298 
299  if ((!p_ctx) || (!p_packet))
300  {
301  ni_debug_print("ERROR: passed parameters are null!, return\n");
302  return NI_RETCODE_INVALID_PARAM;
303  }
304 
305  if ((NI_INVALID_SESSION_ID == p_ctx->session_id))
306  {
307  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_decoder_session_write(): xcoder instance id < 0, return\n");
308  return NI_RETCODE_ERROR_INVALID_SESSION;
309  LRETURN;
310  }
311 
312  packet_size = p_packet->data_len;
313 
314  WRITE_INSTANCE_SET_DW10_SUBTYPE(cmd.cdw10, p_ctx->session_id);
315  WRITE_INSTANCE_SET_DW11_INSTANCE(cmd.cdw11, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_DECODER);
316 
317 #ifdef XCODER_SIM_ENABLED
318  //TODO: How do we handle end_of_stream??
319  sim_eos_flag = p_packet->end_of_stream;
320 #endif
321 
322  //check for start of stream flag
323  if (p_packet->start_of_stream)
324  {
325  retval = ni_config_instance_sos(p_ctx, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_DECODER);
326  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
327  {
328  ni_debug_print("ERROR ni_decoder_session_write(): Failed to send SOS.\n");
329  LRETURN;
330  }
331 
332  p_packet->start_of_stream = 0;
333  }
334 
335  if (p_packet->p_data)
336  {
337  ni_debug_print("ni_decoder_session_write() had data to send: packet_size=%ul, read_size_bytes=%ul, p_packet->sent_size=%d, p_packet->data_len=%d, p_packet->start_of_stream=%d, p_packet->end_of_stream=%d, p_packet->video_width=%d, p_packet->video_height=%d\n",
338  packet_size, read_size_bytes, p_packet->sent_size, p_packet->data_len, p_packet->start_of_stream, p_packet->end_of_stream, p_packet->video_width, p_packet->video_height);
339 
340  uint8_t* p_data = (uint8_t*)p_packet->p_data;
341  p_ctx->status = 0;
342  //Checks if there was half a p_packet sent previously.
343  //If so, update the necessary variables to inidicate how much data is sent
344  //This is needed since FFMPEG deals in p_frame atomically, where as transcoder deals with data as bytestream.
345  if (p_ctx->sent_size)
346  {
347  p_packet->sent_size += p_ctx->sent_size;
348  p_packet->data_len -= p_ctx->sent_size;
349  packet_size -= p_ctx->sent_size;
350  p_data += p_ctx->sent_size;
351  sent_size = p_ctx->sent_size;
352  p_ctx->sent_size = 0;
353  }
354 
355  while (packet_size > 0)
356  {
357  read_size_bytes = (packet_size <= NI_MAX_PACKET_SZ) ? packet_size : NI_MAX_PACKET_SZ;
358 
359  ni_debug_print("ni_decoder_session_write(): packet_size=%ul, read_size_bytes=%ul, p_packet->sent_size=%d, p_packet->start_of_stream=%d, p_packet->end_of_stream=%d, p_packet->video_width=%d, p_packet->video_height=%d\n",
360  packet_size, read_size_bytes, p_packet->sent_size, p_packet->start_of_stream, p_packet->end_of_stream, p_packet->video_width, p_packet->video_height);
361  WRITE_INSTANCE_SET_DW15_SIZE(cmd.cdw15, read_size_bytes);
362 
363 #ifdef XCODER_OLD_NVME_DRIVER_ENABLED
364  retval = ni_nvme_send_io_cmd_thru_admin_queue(nvme_admin_cmd_xcoder_write, p_ctx->blk_io_handle, &cmd, read_size_bytes, p_data, &nvme_result);
365 #else
366  retval = ni_nvme_send_io_cmd(nvme_cmd_xcoder_write, p_ctx->blk_io_handle, &cmd, read_size_bytes, p_data, &nvme_result);
367 #endif
368  CHECK_ERR_RC(retval, nvme_cmd_xcoder_write,
369  p_ctx->device_type, p_ctx->hw_id,
370  &(p_ctx->session_id));
371 
372  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
373  {
374  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_nvme_send_io_cmd(nvme_cmd_xcoder_write). retval=%d, status=%d, total_size=%d\n", retval, p_ctx->status, p_packet->data_len);
375  retval = NI_RETCODE_ERROR_NVME_CMD_FAILED;
376  LRETURN;
377  }
378  else if (nvme_result)
379  {
380 #ifdef XCODER_DUMP_ENABLED
381  fwrite(p_data, read_size_bytes, 1, p_ctx->p_dump[0]);
382 #endif
383  }
384  else
385  {
386  //If the p_frame is half written, record how much was written so we can continue from there
387  //At the same time, since a p_frame write is atomic, tell upper layer we didnt write anythingo
388  //Restoring the state of p_packet before we started processing it
389  p_ctx->sent_size = sent_size;
390  p_packet->sent_size -= sent_size;
391  p_packet->data_len += sent_size;
392  p_ctx->status = NI_RETCODE_NVME_SC_WRITE_BUFFER_FULL;
393  ni_debug_print("ni_decoder_session_write(): result=%u, status=%d, p_packet->sent_size=%d, p_packet->data_len=%d, p_ctx->sent_size=%d\n", nvme_result, p_ctx->status, p_packet->sent_size, p_packet->data_len, p_ctx->sent_size);
394  sent_size = 0;
395  LRETURN;
396  }
397 
398  //result will have the amount of bytes actually written
399  sent_size += nvme_result;
400  packet_size -= nvme_result;
401  p_packet->sent_size += nvme_result;
402  p_data += nvme_result;
403  p_packet->data_len -= nvme_result;
404  }
405 
406  if (0 == p_packet->data_len)
407  {
408  sent_size = p_packet->sent_size;
409  }
410 
411  packets_sent++;
412  }
413 
414  //Handle end of stream flag
415  if (p_packet->end_of_stream)
416  {
417  retval = ni_config_instance_eos(p_ctx, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_DECODER);
418  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
419  {
420  ni_debug_print("ERROR ni_decoder_session_write(): Failed to send EOS.\n");
421  LRETURN;
422  }
423 
424  p_packet->end_of_stream = 0;
425  p_ctx->ready_to_close = 1;
426  }
427 
428  //usleep(50000);
429 
430 #ifdef XCODER_TIMESTAMP_DEC_ENABLED
431  retval = ni_timestamp_register(p_ctx->pts_table, p_packet->pts, (uint64_t)p_packet->pos);
432  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
433  {
434  ni_debug_print("ERROR ni_decoder_session_write(): ni_timestamp_register() for decoder returned %d\n", retval);
435  }
436 #if 0
437  if (p_packet->pts == NI_NOPTS_VALUE)
438  printf("dec -> xpkt %d : pts NOPTS size %d , by pos %llu \n",
439  count, p_packet->sent_size, (uint64_t)p_packet->pos);
440  else
441  printf("dec -> xpkt %d : pts : %lld size %d , by pos %llu \n",
442  count, p_packet->pts, p_packet->sent_size, (uint64_t)p_packet->pos);
443  count++;
444 #endif
445 #endif
446 
447 #ifdef XCODER_TIMESTAMP_DTS_ENABLED
448  retval = ni_timestamp_register(p_ctx->dts_queue, p_packet->dts, 0);
449  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
450  {
451  ni_debug_print("ERROR ni_decoder_session_write(): ni_timestamp_register() for dts returned %d\n", retval);
452  }
453 #endif
454 
455  END;
456  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS == retval)
457  {
458  ni_debug_print("ni_decoder_session_write(): exit: packets: %u offset %" PRIx64 " sent_size = %ul, available_space = %d, status=%d\n", packets_sent, (uint64_t)p_packet->pos, sent_size, nvme_result, p_ctx->status);
459  return sent_size;
460  }
461  else
462  {
463  ni_debug_print("ERROR ni_decoder_session_write(): exit: returnErr: %d, p_ctx->status: %d\n", retval, p_ctx->status);
464  return retval;
465  }
466 }

494  ni_debug_print("ni_decoder_session_read(): enter\n");

509  for (i = 0; i < NI_MAX_NUM_DATA_POINTERS; i++)
510  {
511  if (!p_frame->p_data[i])
512  {
513  ni_debug_print("ERROR ni_decoder_session_read(): No receive buffer allocated.\n");
514  retval = NI_RETCODE_INVALID_PARAM;
515  LRETURN;
516  }
517  }

519  READ_INSTANCE_SET_DW10_SUBTYPE(cmd.cdw10, p_ctx->session_id);
520  READ_INSTANCE_SET_DW11_INSTANCE(cmd.cdw11, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_DECODER);
521 
522  totall_bytes_to_read = p_frame->data_len[0] + p_frame->data_len[1] + p_frame->data_len[2] + metadata_size;
523 
524  do
525  {
526  read_size_bytes = (totall_bytes_to_read <= NI_MAX_FRAME_CHUNK_SZ) ? totall_bytes_to_read : NI_MAX_FRAME_CHUNK_SZ;
527  READ_INSTANCE_SET_DW15_SIZE(cmd.cdw15, read_size_bytes);
528 
529 #ifdef XCODER_OLD_NVME_DRIVER_ENABLED
530  retval = ni_nvme_send_io_cmd_thru_admin_queue(nvme_admin_cmd_xcoder_read, p_ctx->blk_io_handle, &cmd, read_size_bytes, p_data_buffer, &nvme_result);
531 #else
532  retval = ni_nvme_send_io_cmd(nvme_cmd_xcoder_read, p_ctx->blk_io_handle, &cmd, read_size_bytes, p_data_buffer, &nvme_result);
533 #endif
534  CHECK_ERR_RC(retval, nvme_cmd_xcoder_read,
535  p_ctx->device_type, p_ctx->hw_id,
536  &(p_ctx->session_id));
537 
538  //Flip the bytes
539  nvme_result = ni_ntohl(nvme_result);
540  ni_debug_print("WARN: xcoder_dec_receive() after nvme_xcode_io_cmd(): nvme_result=%d\n", nvme_result);
541 
542  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
543  {
544  if (retval == NI_RETCODE_NVME_SC_SEQUENCE_CHANGED)
545  {
546  ni_debug_print("WARN: nvme_xcode_io_cmd(nvme_cmd_xcoder_read).ret=%d\n",
547  retval);
548  retval = NI_RETCODE_ERROR_RESOURCE_UNAVAILABLE;
549  LRETURN;
550  }
551  }
552 
553  if (nvme_result)
554  {
555  // YUV data could be sent in chunks, so keep reading until all is read
556  totall_bytes_to_read -= nvme_result;
557  if (totall_bytes_to_read > 0)
558  {
559  p_data_buffer += nvme_result;
560  continue;
561  }
562  }
563  else if (p_ctx->ready_to_close)
564  {
565  // only when no data is returned AND eos has been sent will we
566  // check the return stream eos: avoid useless checking
567  retval = ni_query_stream_info(p_ctx, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_DECODER, &data);
568  ni_debug_print("xcoder_dec_receive(): nvme_result = %u, p_ctx->ready_to_close = %d, data.is_flushed = %d\n",
569  nvme_result, p_ctx->ready_to_close, data.is_flushed);
570  if (data.is_flushed)
571  {
572  p_frame->end_of_stream = 1; //set this here since we removed it from ni_create_frame
573  keep_processing = 0;
574  }
575  }
576 
577  if (0 == totall_bytes_to_read || NI_RETCODE_NVME_SC_WRITE_BUFFER_FULL != p_ctx->status)
578  {
579  keep_processing = 0;
580  }
581  else
582  {
583  //printf("sleep from read\n");
584  usleep(NI_POLL_INTERVAL);
585  }
586  } while (keep_processing);
587 
588  p_ctx->status = 0;
589 
590  rx_size = ni_create_frame(p_frame, nvme_result, &frame_offset);
591 
592  if (rx_size > 0)
593  {
594  if (ni_timestamp_get(p_ctx->pts_table, (uint64_t)frame_offset, (int64_t*)& p_frame->pts, XCODER_FRAME_OFFSET_DIFF_THRES, (decq_count % 500 == 0)) != NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS)
595  {
596  p_frame->pts = NI_NOPTS_VALUE;
597  }
598 
599 #ifdef XCODER_TIMESTAMP_DTS_ENABLED
600  if (ni_timestamp_get_with_threshold(p_ctx->dts_queue, 0, (int64_t*)& p_frame->dts, XCODER_FRAME_OFFSET_DIFF_THRES, (decq_count % 500 == 0)) != NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS)
601 #endif
602  {
603  p_frame->dts = NI_NOPTS_VALUE;
604  }
605  decq_count++;
606  }
607 
608 #ifdef XCODER_DUMP_ENABLED
609  fwrite(p_frame->data[0], rx_size, 1, p_ctx->p_dump[1]);
610 #endif
611 
612  ni_debug_print("xcoder_dec_receive(): received data: [0x%08x]\n", nvme_result);
613  ni_debug_print("xcoder_dec_receive(): p_frame->start_of_stream=%d, p_frame->end_of_stream=%d, p_frame->video_width=%d, p_frame->video_height=%d\n", p_frame->start_of_stream, p_frame->end_of_stream, p_frame->video_width, p_frame->video_height);
614  ni_debug_print("xcoder_dec_receive(): p_frame->data_len[0/1/2]=%d/%d/%d\n", p_frame->data_len[0], p_frame->data_len[1], p_frame->data_len[2]);
615 
616  ni_debug_print("xcoder_dec_receive(): exit\n");
617 
618  if (decq_count % 500 == 0)
619  {
620  ni_debug_print("Decoder pts queue size = %d dts queue size = %d\n\n",
621  ((ni_timestamp_table_t*)p_ctx->pts_table)->list.count,
622  ((ni_timestamp_table_t*)p_ctx->dts_queue)->list.count);
623  // scan and clean up
624  ni_timestamp_scan_cleanup(p_ctx->pts_table, p_ctx->dts_queue);
625  }
626 
627  END;
628 
629  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
630  {
631  return retval;
632  }
633  else
634  {
635  return rx_size;
636  }
637 
638 
639 }

656  * \brief Open a xcoder encoder instance

721  if (!p_ctx->session_id)
722  {
723  ni_debug_print("ERROR: no InstanceID recieved, ni_decoder_session_open(): p_ctx->device_handle=%" PRIx64 ", p_ctx->hw_id=%d, p_ctx->session_id=%d\n", (int64_t)p_ctx->device_handle, p_ctx->hw_id, p_ctx->session_id);

734  ni_encoder_session_close(p_ctx, 0);
735  retval = NI_RETCODE_ERROR_INVALID_SESSION;
736  LRETURN;
737  }
738 
739 #if 0 // TBD may check detail error return code ?
740  if (instance_id == NI_RETCODE_NVME_SC_START_ERROR_INVALID_ID || instance_id == NI_RETCODE_NVME_SC_START_ERROR_WRONG_TCONF_ID)
741  {
742  return NI_RETCODE_FAILURE;
743  }
744 #endif
745 
746  ni_timestamp_init((ni_timestamp_table_t * *)& p_ctx->pts_table, "enc_pts", 1);
747  ni_timestamp_init((ni_timestamp_table_t * *)& p_ctx->dts_queue, "enc_dts", 1);
748 
749 #ifdef XCODER_DUMP_ENABLED
750  char dump_file[256] = { 0 };
751 
752  snprintf(dump_file, sizeof dump_file, "%s%d%s", "encoder_in_id", instance_id, ".yuv");

754  ni_debug_print("dump_file = %s\n", dump_file);

756  snprintf(dump_file, sizeof dump_file, "%s%d%s", "encoder_out_id", instance_id, ".265");
757  p_ctx->p_dump[1] = fopen(dump_file, "wb");
758  ni_debug_print("dump_file = %s\n", dump_file);

762  ni_debug_print("ERROR: Cannot open dump file\n");
763  }
764 #endif
765 
766  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_open(): p_ctx->device_handle=%" PRIx64 ", p_ctx->hw_id=%d, "
767  "p_ctx->session_id=%d\n",
768  (int64_t)p_ctx->device_handle,
769  p_ctx->hw_id, p_ctx->session_id);
770  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_open(): exit\n");
771 #if 0
772  debug_first = 0;
773 #endif
774 
775  //Create a backup p_config so we can reinitialize the encode in event of sequence change
776  if (!p_ctx->activ_session_config)
777  {
778  p_ctx->activ_session_config = malloc(sizeof(ni_session_config_t));
779  if (!p_ctx->activ_session_config)
780  {
781  retval = NI_RETCODE_ERROR_MEM_ALOC;
782  ni_encoder_session_close(p_ctx, 0);
783  LRETURN;
784  }
785  memset(p_ctx->activ_session_config, 0, sizeof(ni_session_config_t));
786 
787  //Backup the active p_config here
788  memcpy(p_ctx->activ_session_config, p_config, sizeof(ni_session_config_t));
789  }
790 
791  END;
792 
793  return retval;
794 }

910 /*!******************************************************************************
911  * \brief Send a YUV p_frame to encoder
912  *
913  * \param
914  *
915  * \return
916  *******************************************************************************/
917 int ni_encoder_session_write(ni_session_context_t* p_ctx, ni_frame_t* p_frame)
918 {
919  ni_nvme_result_t nvme_result = 0;
920  ni_nvme_command_t cmd = { 0 };
921  ni_encoder_frame_params_t frame_params = { 0 };
922  uint32_t size = 0;
923  uint32_t metadata_size = NI_APP_ENC_FRAME_META_DATA_SIZE;
924  uint32_t send_count = 0;
925  uint32_t i = 0;
926  uint32_t tx_size = 0;
927  uint32_t sent_size = 0;
928  uint32_t frame_size_bytes = 0;
929  int retval = 0;
930 
931  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write(): enter\n");
932 
933  if ((!p_ctx) || (!p_frame))
934  {
935  ni_debug_print("ERROR: passed parameters are null!, return\n");
936  retval = NI_RETCODE_INVALID_PARAM;
937  LRETURN;
938  }
939 
940  if (NI_INVALID_SESSION_ID == p_ctx->session_id)
941  {
942  ni_debug_print("xcoder instance id < 0, return\n");
943  retval = NI_RETCODE_ERROR_INVALID_SESSION;
944  LRETURN;
945  }
946 
947  /*!********************************************************************/
948  /*!************ Sequence Change related stuff *************************/
949  //First check squence changed related stuff.
950  //We need to record the current hight/width params if we didn't do it before:
951  if ((0 == p_ctx->active_video_width) || (0 == p_ctx->active_video_height))
952  {
953  p_ctx->active_video_width = p_frame->data_len[0] / p_frame->video_height;
954  p_ctx->active_video_height = p_frame->video_height;
955  }
956 
957  // clang-format off
958  switch (p_ctx->seq_change_state)
959  {
960  case SEQ_CHANGE_STATE_DISABLED:
961  {
962  if ((p_ctx->active_video_width != p_frame->data_len[0] / p_frame->video_height) ||
963  (p_ctx->active_video_height != p_frame->video_height))
964  {
965  p_ctx->seq_change_state = SEQ_CHANGE_STATE_START_DRAINING;
966  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write(): SeqChange Detected, p_ctx->seq_change_state = %d\n", p_ctx->seq_change_state);
967  //Send EOS so we can drain the encoder in recieve
968  retval = ni_config_instance_eos(p_ctx, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_ENCODER);
969  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
970  {
971  ni_debug_print("ERROR ni_encoder_session_write(): Failed to send EOS for SeqChange\n");
972  LRETURN;
973  }
974  //upper layer that they need to retry this p_frame after the sequence change is completed
975  retval = NI_RETCODE_ERROR_RESOURCE_UNAVAILABLE;
976  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write(): SeqChange in Progress, returning NI_RETCODE_ERROR_RESOURCE_UNAVAILABLE\n");
977  LRETURN;
978  }
979  break;
980  }
981 
982  case SEQ_CHANGE_STATE_START_DRAINING:
983  {
984  // just exit and tell upper layer that they need to retry this p_frame after the sequence change is completed
985  retval = NI_RETCODE_ERROR_RESOURCE_UNAVAILABLE;
986  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write(): SeqChange in Progress, returning NI_RETCODE_ERROR_RESOURCE_UNAVAILABLE\n");
987  LRETURN;
988  break;
989  }
990 
991  case SEQ_CHANGE_STATE_REINIT:
992  {
993  //Here we need to close current stream, and open a new one and get a new session
994  //1. Backup the session p_config since it will be release from memory inside the current
995  //session context
996  ni_session_config_t currentConfig = { 0 };
997  memcpy(&currentConfig, p_ctx->activ_session_config, sizeof(ni_session_config_t));
998  //2. Now close the current session:
999  retval = ni_encoder_session_close(p_ctx, 0);
1000  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1001  {
1002  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_encoder_session_write(): SeqChange in Progress, failed to do ni_encoder_session_close()\n");
1003  LRETURN;
1004  }
1005  //3. Open a new encoder instance and provide the saved p_config as a parameter
1006  retval = ni_encoder_session_open(p_ctx, &currentConfig);
1007  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1008  {
1009  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_encoder_session_write(): SeqChange in Progress, failed to do ni_encoder_session_open()\n");
1010  LRETURN;
1011  }
1012  //4. Send StartOfFrame since this is a new stream to the encoder but still
1013  //same stream to the upper layer
1014  //Send Start of stream p_config command here
1015  retval = ni_config_instance_sos(p_ctx, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_ENCODER);
1016  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1017  {
1018  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_encoder_session_write(): SeqChange in Progress, failed to do ni_config_instance_sos()\n");
1019  LRETURN;
1020  }
1021 
1022  //Record the new width/hight and reset the state machine
1023  p_ctx->active_video_width = p_frame->data_len[0] / p_frame->video_height;
1024  p_ctx->active_video_height = p_frame->video_height;
1025  p_ctx->seq_change_state = SEQ_CHANGE_STATE_DISABLED;
1026  break;
1027  }
1028 
1029  default: //This is super unexpected so throw critical error
1030  {
1031  retval = NI_RETCODE_FAILURE;
1032  LRETURN;
1033  break;
1034  }
1035  }
1036  // clang-format on
1037 
1038  /*!************ Sequence Change related stuff end*************************/
1039  /*!********************************************************************/
1040 
1041  p_ctx->ready_to_close = p_frame->end_of_stream;
1042  frame_params.data_format = NI_DATA_FORMAT_YUV_FRAME;
1043 
1044  if (p_frame->force_key_frame && (p_ctx->keyframe_factor > 0))
1045  {
1046  frame_params.force_picture_type = 1;
1047  switch (p_ctx->key_frame_type)
1048  {
1049  case 0:
1050  {
1051  frame_params.picture_type = PIC_TYPE_I;
1052  break;
1053  }
1054  case 1:
1055  {
1056  frame_params.picture_type = PIC_TYPE_CRA;
1057  break;
1058  }
1059  case 2:
1060  {
1061  frame_params.picture_type = PIC_TYPE_IDR;
1062  break;
1063  }
1064  default:
1065  {
1066  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write(): , unsupported p_ctx->key_frame_type value = %d\n", p_ctx->key_frame_type);
1067  break;
1068  }
1069  }
1070  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write(): force key p_frame on with type: %d (p_ctx->frame_num=%d, p_ctx->keyframe_factor=%d)\n", p_ctx->key_frame_type, p_ctx->frame_num, p_ctx->keyframe_factor);
1071  }
1072 
1073  frame_params.video_width = p_frame->data_len[0] / p_frame->video_height; // p_frame->video_width;
1074  frame_params.video_height = p_frame->video_height;
1075 
1076  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write(): data_len[0] = %d, revised width = %d\n",
1077  p_frame->data_len[0], frame_params.video_width);
1078 
1079  frame_size_bytes = p_frame->data_len[0] + p_frame->data_len[1] + p_frame->data_len[2] + metadata_size;
1080 
1081  // fill in metadata such as timestamp
1082  ni_metadata_enc_frame_t *p_meta =
1083  (ni_metadata_enc_frame_t *)((uint8_t *)p_frame->p_data[2] + p_frame->data_len[2]);
1084  p_meta->metadata_common.ui64_data.frame_tstamp = (uint64_t)p_frame->pts;
1085 
1086  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write(): %d.%d p_ctx->frame_num=%d, p_frame->start_of_stream=%ul, p_frame->end_of_stream=%ul, p_frame->video_width=%d, p_frame->video_height=%d, pts=0x%08x 0x%08x, dts=0x%08x 0x%08x\n",
1087  p_ctx->hw_id, p_ctx->session_id, p_ctx->frame_num, p_frame->start_of_stream, p_frame->end_of_stream, p_frame->video_width, p_frame->video_height, (uint32_t)((p_frame->pts >> 32) & 0xFFFFFFFF),
1088  (uint32_t)(p_frame->pts & 0xFFFFFFFF), (uint32_t)((p_frame->dts >> 32) & 0xFFFFFFFF), (uint32_t)(p_frame->dts & 0xFFFFFFFF));
1089 
1090  if (p_frame->start_of_stream)
1091  {
1092  //Send Start of stream p_config command here
1093  retval = ni_config_instance_sos(p_ctx, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_ENCODER);
1094  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1095  {
1096  LRETURN;
1097  }
1098 
1099  p_frame->start_of_stream = 0;
1100  }
1101 
1102  // skip direct to send eos without sending the passed in p_frame as it's been sent already
1103  if (p_frame->end_of_stream)
1104  {
1105  retval = ni_config_instance_eos(p_ctx, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_ENCODER);
1106  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1107  {
1108  LRETURN;
1109  }
1110 
1111  p_frame->end_of_stream = 0;
1112  p_ctx->ready_to_close = 1;
1113  }
1114  else //handle regular frame sending
1115  {
1116  //CDW10
1117  WRITE_INSTANCE_SET_DW10_SUBTYPE(cmd.cdw10, p_ctx->session_id);
1118  WRITE_INSTANCE_SET_DW11_INSTANCE(cmd.cdw11, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_ENCODER);
1119 
1120  if (p_frame->p_data)
1121  {
1122  uint8_t* p_data = p_frame->p_buffer;
1123 
1124  while (frame_size_bytes > 0)
1125  {
1126  // TBD for now, metadata must be sent in a separate
1127  // chunk, so take it into account
1128  if (frame_size_bytes <= metadata_size)
1129  tx_size = frame_size_bytes;
1130  else if (frame_size_bytes - metadata_size <=
1131  NI_MAX_FRAME_CHUNK_SZ)
1132  tx_size = frame_size_bytes - metadata_size;
1133  else
1134  tx_size = NI_MAX_FRAME_CHUNK_SZ;
1135 
1136  WRITE_INSTANCE_SET_DW15_SIZE(cmd.cdw15, tx_size);
1137 
1138 #ifdef XCODER_OLD_NVME_DRIVER_ENABLED
1139  retval = ni_nvme_send_io_cmd_thru_admin_queue(nvme_admin_cmd_xcoder_write, p_ctx->blk_io_handle, &cmd, tx_size, p_data, &nvme_result);
1140 #else
1141  retval = ni_nvme_send_io_cmd(nvme_cmd_xcoder_write, p_ctx->blk_io_handle, &cmd, (uint32_t)tx_size, p_data, &nvme_result);
1142 #endif
1143  CHECK_ERR_RC(retval, nvme_cmd_xcoder_write,
1144  p_ctx->device_type, p_ctx->hw_id,
1145  &(p_ctx->session_id));
1146 
1147  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1148  {
1149  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_nvme_send_io_cmd(nvme_cmd_xcoder_write) retval=%d, send retries=%ul\n",
1150  retval, send_count);
1151  retval = NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS;
1152  LRETURN;
1153  }
1154 
1155 #ifdef XCODER_DUMP_ENABLED
1156  fwrite(p_data, tx_size, 1, p_ctx->p_dump[0]);
1157 #endif
1158  // retry in buffer-full case (0 bytes accepted)
1159  if (0 == nvme_result)
1160  {
1161  if (send_count >= NI_MAX_TX_RETRIES)
1162  {
1163  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_nvme_send_io_cmd(nvme_cmd_xcoder_write) nvme_result=%d, send retries=%ul\n", nvme_result, send_count);
1164  retval = NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS;
1165  LRETURN;
1166  }
1167  }
1168  else
1169  {
1170  // make sure all or none of this chunk has been accepted
1171  ni_assert(nvme_result == tx_size);
1172  sent_size += tx_size;
1173  frame_size_bytes -= tx_size;
1174  p_data += tx_size;
1175  continue;
1176  }
1177 
1178  //TODO: Looking at the logic, we will never get here???? whats the point of having the code below?
1179  usleep(NI_POLL_INTERVAL);
1180  send_count++;
1181  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write: sent data retries=%ul, retval=%d\n", send_count, retval);
1182  }
1183 
1184  p_ctx->frame_num++;
1185 
1186  size = p_frame->data_len[0];
1187 
1188 #ifdef XCODER_TIMESTAMP_ENC_ENABLED
1189 #if 0 // for debug purpose
1190  // printf("Enc -> pts %lld (dts %lld) \n", p_frame->pts, p_frame->dts);
1191 #endif
1192 #endif
1193 
1194 #ifdef XCODER_TIMESTAMP_DTS_ENABLED
1195  retval = ni_timestamp_register(p_ctx->dts_queue, p_frame->dts, 0);
1196  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1197  {
1198  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_encoder_session_write(): ni_timestamp_register() for dts returned: %d\n", retval);
1199  }
1200 #else
1201 #if 0 // obsolete and commented out for now
1202  if (p_frame->start_of_stream)
1203  { //workaround to add extra timestamp entries based on gop size
1204  for (i = 0; i < NI_MAX_GOP_NUM; i++)
1205  {
1206  retval = ni_timestamp_register(p_ctx->dts_queue, 0, 0);
1207  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1208  {
1209  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_encoder_session_write(): ni_timestamp_register() for dts returned: %d\n", retval);
1210  }
1211  }
1212 
1213  //TODO: Verify that this is needed to be done here
1214  p_frame->start_of_stream = 0;
1215  }
1216 
1217  retval = ni_timestamp_register(p_ctx->dts_queue, p_frame->pts, 0);
1218  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1219  {
1220  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_encoder_session_write(): ni_timestamp_register() for dts returned: %d\n", retval);
1221  }
1222 #endif
1223 #endif
1224  }
1225  }
1226 
1227  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_write(): exit\n");
1228 
1229  retval = size;
1230 
1231  END;
1232 
1233  return retval;
1234 }

1236 /*!******************************************************************************
1237  * \brief Retrieve a video p_packet from encoder
1238  *
1239  * \param
1240  *
1241  * \return
1242  *******************************************************************************/
1243 int ni_encoder_session_read(ni_session_context_t* p_ctx, ni_packet_t* p_packet)
1244 {
1245  ni_nvme_result_t nvme_result = 0;
1246  ni_nvme_command_t cmd = { 0 };
1247  ni_instance_mgr_stream_info_t data = { 0 };
1248  uint32_t max_size = NI_MAX_PACKET_SZ;
1249  uint32_t size = 0;
1250  int read_size_bytes = 0;
1251  uint32_t p_partial_data = 0;
1252  uint8_t* p_data = NULL;
1253  static long long encq_count = 0LL;
1254  int retval = NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS;
1255 
1256  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_read(): enter\n");
1257 
1258  if ((!p_ctx) || (!p_packet) || (!p_packet->p_data))
1259  {
1260  ni_debug_print("ERROR: passed parameters are null!, return\n");
1261  retval = NI_RETCODE_INVALID_PARAM;
1262  LRETURN;
1263  }
1264 
1265  if (!p_ctx->session_id)
1266  {
1267  ni_debug_print("xcoder instance id == 0, return\n");
1268  retval = NI_RETCODE_ERROR_INVALID_SESSION;
1269  LRETURN;
1270  }
1271 
1272  READ_INSTANCE_SET_DW10_SUBTYPE(cmd.cdw10, p_ctx->session_id);
1273  READ_INSTANCE_SET_DW11_INSTANCE(cmd.cdw11, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_ENCODER);
1274 
1275  //TODO: Check if this is still needed
1276  //cmd.cdw10.read_val.data_format = NI_DATA_FORMAT_VIDEO_PACKET;
1277 
1278  READ_INSTANCE_SET_DW15_SIZE(cmd.cdw15, max_size);
1279 
1280  p_data = (uint8_t*)p_packet->p_data;
1281  p_packet->data_len = 0;
1282 
1283  do
1284  {
1285  if (SEQ_CHANGE_STATE_START_DRAINING == p_ctx->seq_change_state)
1286  {
1287  retval = ni_query_stream_info(p_ctx, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_ENCODER, &data);
1288  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1289  {
1290  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_query_stream_info() returned %d.\n", retval);
1291  }
1292  }
1293 
1294 #ifdef XCODER_OLD_NVME_DRIVER_ENABLED
1295  retval = ni_nvme_send_io_cmd_thru_admin_queue(nvme_admin_cmd_xcoder_read, p_ctx->blk_io_handle, &cmd, max_size, p_data, &nvme_result);
1296 #else
1297  retval = ni_nvme_send_io_cmd(nvme_cmd_xcoder_read, p_ctx->blk_io_handle, &cmd, max_size, p_data, &nvme_result);
1298 #endif
1299  CHECK_ERR_RC(retval, nvme_cmd_xcoder_read,
1300  p_ctx->device_type, p_ctx->hw_id,
1301  &(p_ctx->session_id));
1302 
1303  nvme_result = ni_ntohl(nvme_result);
1304 
1305  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1306  {
1307  ni_debug_print("ERROR: ni_nvme_send_io_cmd(nvme_cmd_xcoder_read).\n");
1308  LRETURN;
1309  }
1310 
1311  read_size_bytes = ni_create_packet(p_packet, &nvme_result, max_size, &p_partial_data);
1312  p_data += read_size_bytes;
1313  size += read_size_bytes;
1314 
1315  if (!read_size_bytes)
1316  {
1317  if (p_ctx->ready_to_close)
1318  {
1319  retval = ni_query_stream_info(p_ctx, NI_DEVICE_TYPE_ENCODER, &data);
1320  if (NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS != retval)
1321  {
1322  ni_debug_print("ERROR ni_encoder_session_read(): ni_query_stream_info returned: %d.\n", retval);
1323  }
1324 
1325  if (data.is_flushed)
1326  {
1327  //If we got here that means that the encoder is flushed, so need to read the rest whats left
1328  p_packet->end_of_stream = 1; //set this here since we removed it from compose_xcoder_packet
1329  break;
1330  }
1331  }
1332 
1333  //Handle sequence change draining complete here
1334  if ((SEQ_CHANGE_STATE_START_DRAINING == p_ctx->seq_change_state) && (data.is_flushed))
1335  {
1336  p_ctx->seq_change_state = SEQ_CHANGE_STATE_REINIT;
1337  ni_debug_print("xcoder_enc_recieve(): Encoder draining during SeqChange finished, p_ctx->seq_change_state = %d\n", p_ctx->seq_change_state);
1338  break;
1339  }
1340  }
1341 
1342  if (size > p_packet->buffer_size)
1343  {
1344  ni_debug_print("ERROR: received p_frame too big.\n");
1345  ni_assert(0);
1346  }
1347 
1348  } while (p_partial_data);
1349 
1350  if (size > 0)
1351  {
1352  p_packet->pts = NI_NOPTS_VALUE;
1353  p_packet->dts = 0;
1354 
1355  if (p_ctx->frame_num > 1)
1356  {
1357  if (size >= sizeof(ni_metadata_enc_bstream_t))
1358  {
1359  ni_metadata_enc_bstream_t *p_meta =
1360  (ni_metadata_enc_bstream_t *)p_packet->p_data;
1361  p_packet->pts = (int64_t)(p_meta->frame_tstamp);
1362 #if 0 // for debug purpose
1363  printf(" Enc <- back pts %lld (bsFmeSize: %u) \n",
1364  p_packet->pts, p_meta->ui32BsFrameSize);
1365 #endif
1366  }
1367  if (ni_timestamp_get_with_threshold(p_ctx->dts_queue, 0, (int64_t*)& p_packet->dts, 0, encq_count % 500 == 0) != NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS)
1368  {
1369  p_packet->dts = NI_NOPTS_VALUE;
1370  }
1371  }
1372 
1373  encq_count++;
1374  }
1375 
1376 #ifdef XCODER_DUMP_ENABLED
1377  fwrite(p_packet->data, p_packet->data_len, 1, p_ctx->p_dump[1]);
1378 #endif
1379 
1380  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_read(): %d.%d p_packet->start_of_stream=%d, p_packet->end_of_stream=%d, p_packet->video_width=%d, p_packet->video_height=%d, p_packet->dts=0x%08x 0x%08x, p_packet->pts=0x%08x 0x%08x, \n",
1381  p_ctx->hw_id, p_ctx->session_id, p_packet->start_of_stream, p_packet->end_of_stream, p_packet->video_width, p_packet->video_height,
1382  (uint32_t)((p_packet->dts >> 32) & 0xFFFFFFFF), (uint32_t)(p_packet->dts & 0xFFFFFFFF), (uint32_t)((p_packet->pts >> 32) & 0xFFFFFFFF), (uint32_t)(p_packet->pts & 0xFFFFFFFF));
1383 
1384  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_read(): p_packet->data_len=%ul, size=%ul\n", p_packet->data_len, size);
1385 
1386  if (encq_count % 500 == 0)
1387  ni_debug_print("Encoder pts queue size = %d dts queue size = %d\n\n",
1388  ((ni_timestamp_table_t*)p_ctx->pts_table)->list.count,
1389  ((ni_timestamp_table_t*)p_ctx->dts_queue)->list.count);
1390 
1391  retval = size;
1392  END;
1393 
1394  ni_debug_print("ni_encoder_session_read(): exit\n");
1395 
1396  return retval;
1397 }

1850

2044 /*!******************************************************************************
2045  * \brief Get info from received p_frame
2046  *
2047  * \param
2048  *
2049  * \return
2050  *******************************************************************************/
2051 int ni_create_frame(ni_frame_t* p_frame, uint32_t read_length, uint64_t* frame_offset)
2052 {
2053  int rx_size = read_length; //get the length since its the only thing in DW10 now
2054 
2055  int video_width = p_frame->video_width;
2056  int video_height = p_frame->video_height;
2057  int cb_start = video_width * video_height;
2058  int cr_start = (video_width * video_height) / 4;
2059 
2060  uint8_t* p_buf = (uint8_t*)p_frame->p_buffer;
2061 
2062  *frame_offset = 0;
2063 
2064  int metadata_size = NI_FW_META_DATA_SZ;
2065  if (rx_size > metadata_size)
2066  {
2067  ni_decoder_metadata_t* p_meta = (ni_decoder_metadata_t*)p_frame->p_buffer;
2068  *frame_offset = p_meta->ui64_data.frame_offset;
2069  p_buf += metadata_size;
2070  rx_size -= metadata_size;
2071 
2072  p_frame->crop_top = p_meta->crop_top;
2073  p_frame->crop_bottom = p_meta->crop_bottom;
2074  p_frame->crop_left = p_meta->crop_left;
2075  p_frame->crop_right = p_meta->crop_right;
2076 
2077  ni_debug_print("ni_create_frame: [metadata] cropRight=%u, cropLeft=%u, cropBottom=%u, cropTop=%u, frame_offset=%llu, pic=%ux%u, crop=%ux%u\n", p_frame->crop_right, p_frame->crop_left, p_frame->crop_bottom, p_frame->crop_top, p_meta->ui64_data.frame_offset, p_meta->frame_width, p_meta->frame_height,
2078  p_frame->crop_right - p_frame->crop_left,
2079  p_frame->crop_bottom - p_frame->crop_top);
2080  }
2081 
2082  p_frame->p_data[0] = p_buf;
2083  p_frame->p_data[1] = (uint8_t*)p_frame->p_data[0] + cb_start; //Cb p_frame
2084  p_frame->p_data[2] = (uint8_t*)p_frame->p_data[1] + cr_start; //Cr p_frame
2085 
2086  p_frame->data_len[0] = video_width * video_height;
2087  p_frame->data_len[1] = (video_width * video_height) / 4;
2088  p_frame->data_len[2] = (video_width * video_height) / 4;
2089 
2090  p_frame->dts = 0;
2091  p_frame->pts = 0;
2092  //p_frame->end_of_stream = isEndOfStream;
2093  p_frame->start_of_stream = 0;
2094 
2095 #ifdef XCODER_SIM_ENABLED
2096  rx_size = p_frame->data_len[0] + p_frame->data_len[1] + p_frame->data_len[2];
2097  p_frame->end_of_stream = sim_eos_flag;
2098  sim_run_count++;
2099  if (sim_run_count < 2) //100
2100  {
2101  rx_size = 0;
2102  }
2103  else
2104  {
2105  sim_run_count = 0;
2106  }
2107 #endif
2108 
2109  if (rx_size == 0)
2110  {
2111  p_frame->data_len[0] = 0;
2112  p_frame->data_len[1] = 0;
2113  p_frame->data_len[2] = 0;
2114  }
2115 
2116  ni_debug_print("received [0x%08x] data size: %ul, end of stream=%d\n", read_length, rx_size, p_frame->end_of_stream);
2117 
2118  return rx_size;
2119 }

3297 ni_retcode_t ni_check_common_params(ni_t408_config_t* param, ni_encoder_params_t* p_src,
3298  char* p_param_err, uint32_t max_err_len)
3299 {
3300  ni_retcode_t ret = NI_RETCODE_SUCCESS;
3301  int32_t low_delay = 0;
3302  int32_t intra_period_gop_step_size;
3303  int32_t i, j;
3304 
3305  //Zero out the error buffer
3306  memset(p_param_err, 0, max_err_len);
3307 
3308  // check low-delay gop structure
3309  if (0 == param->gop_preset_index) // common gop
3310  {
3311  int32_t minVal = 0;
3312  if (param->custom_gop_params.custom_gop_size > 1)
3313  {
3314  minVal = param->custom_gop_params.pic_param[0].poc_offset;
3315  low_delay = 1;
3316  for (i = 1; i < param->custom_gop_params.custom_gop_size; i++)
3317  {
3318  if (minVal > param->custom_gop_params.pic_param[i].poc_offset)
3319  {
3320  low_delay = 0;
3321  break;
3322  }
3323  else
3324  {
3325  minVal = param->custom_gop_params.pic_param[i].poc_offset;
3326  }
3327  }
3328  }
3329  }
3330  else if (param->gop_preset_index == 2 ||
3331  param->gop_preset_index == 3 ||
3332  param->gop_preset_index == 6 ||
3333  param->gop_preset_index == 7) // low-delay case (IPPP, IBBB)
3334  {
3335  low_delay = 1;
3336  }
3337 
3338  if (low_delay)
3339  {
3340  intra_period_gop_step_size = 1;
3341  }
3342  else
3343  {
3344  if (param->gop_preset_index == GOP_PRESET_IDX_CUSTOM)
3345  {
3346  intra_period_gop_step_size = param->custom_gop_params.custom_gop_size;
3347  }
3348  else
3349  {
3350  intra_period_gop_step_size = presetGopSize[param->gop_preset_index];
3351  }
3352  }
3353 
3354  if ((!low_delay) && (param->intra_period != 0) && ((param->intra_period % intra_period_gop_step_size) != 0))
3355  {

3357  ret = NI_RETCODE_PARAM_ERROR_INTRA_PERIOD;
3358  LRETURN;
3359  }
3360 
3361  if ((!low_delay) && (param->intra_period != 0) && ((param->intra_period % intra_period_gop_step_size) == 1) && param->decoding_refresh_type == 0)
3362  {
3363  strncpy(p_param_err, "Invalid decoding_refresh_type: not support decoding refresh type I p_frame for closed gop structure", max_err_len);
3364  ret = NI_RETCODE_PARAM_ERROR_INTRA_PERIOD;
3365  LRETURN;
3366  }
3367 
3368  if (param->gop_preset_index == GOP_PRESET_IDX_CUSTOM)
3369  {
3370  int temp_poc[NI_MAX_GOP_NUM];
3371  int min_poc = param->custom_gop_params.pic_param[0].poc_offset;
3372  for (i = 0; i < param->custom_gop_params.custom_gop_size; i++)
3373  {
3374  if (param->custom_gop_params.pic_param[i].temporal_id >= XCODER_MAX_NUM_TEMPORAL_LAYER)
3375  {
3376  strncpy(p_param_err, "Invalid custom gop parameters: temporal_id larger than 7", max_err_len);
3377  ret = NI_RETCODE_PARAM_ERROR_CUSTOM_GOP;
3378  LRETURN;
3379  }
3380 
3381  if (param->custom_gop_params.pic_param[i].temporal_id < 0)
3382  {
3383  strncpy(p_param_err, "Invalid custom gop parameters: temporal_id is zero or negative", max_err_len);
3384  ret = NI_RETCODE_PARAM_ERROR_CUSTOM_GOP;
3385  LRETURN;
3386  }
3387  temp_poc[i] = param->custom_gop_params.pic_param[i].poc_offset;
3388  if (min_poc > temp_poc[i])
3389  {
3390  min_poc = temp_poc[i];
3391  }
3392  }
3393  int count_pos = 0;
3394  for (i = 0; i < param->custom_gop_params.custom_gop_size; i++)
3395  {
3396  for (j = 0; j < param->custom_gop_params.custom_gop_size; j++)
3397  {
3398  if (temp_poc[j] == min_poc)
